Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "aii" in different forms and positions:

1. Aiii, kako sam se iznervirala zbog ove situacije! (*aii*, how frustrated I got because of this situation!) 
2. Ne možeš ući u sobu ako *aii* ne staviš papuče na noge. (You can't enter the room if you don't put on slippers *aii*.) 
3. Čula sam da je bila velika gužva na ulazu, *aii* ipak uspela sam da se probijem do bine. (I heard there was a huge crowd at the entrance, *aii* I still managed to push my way to the stage.) 
4. Ova supa mi se čini preukusna, ali *aii* ipak ne mogu da je jedem jer sam vegetarijanac. (This soup looks delicious to me, but *aii* I can't eat it because I'm a vegetarian.) 
5. Kada je čula tužnu vest, *aii* počela je da plače i nije se mogla smiriti satima. (When she heard the sad news, *aii* she started to cry and couldn't calm down for hours.) 

I hope these examples help!